### Decision: Phase 1.3 (Agent Classes) complete for cowork-orchestrator:

1. base-agent.ts — Abstract BaseAgent c

**Date:** 2026-02-17
**Context:** Phase 1
**Decision:** Phase 1.3 (Agent Classes) complete for cowork-orchestrator:

1. base-agent.ts — Abstract BaseAgent class: config-driven (AgentConfig), status tracking, currentTasks Map, canHandle (capability name matching), getLoad (ratio), assignTask/completeTask/failTask lifecycle, onMessage (overridable no-op), getStats (completed/failed/avgTime/errorRate). Optional setMessageBus/setHistory integration. Uses eventemitter3.

2. claude-agent.ts — ClaudeAgent extends BaseAgent: takes Anthropic client instance, execute() builds messages from conversation history + task, calls API with retry on 429/500/529 (3 retries, exponential delays), extracts text + tool_use blocks, tracks token usage, auto-trims history to 80% of model context limit. chat() single-turn convenience method. Anthropic SDK types: Anthropic.MessageParam, Anthropic.Tool, Anthropic.Message, Anthropic.APIError all accessible from default import namespace.

3. tool-agent.ts — ToolAgent extends ClaudeAgent: manages ToolDefinition[], overrides execute() with tool_use loop (max 10 iterations), converts ToolDefinition.inputSchema to Anthropic.Tool format, stub tool execution returns tool name + input as JSON string, sends tool_result blocks back to Claude until final text response. registerTool/removeTool.

4. human-in-the-loop.ts — HumanInTheLoopAgent extends BaseAgent: approval gate pattern, execute() returns Promise waiting for approve()/reject() calls, configurable timeout (default 5min) auto-rejects, emits 'approval-needed' event, getPendingApprovals(), onApprovalNeeded() listener helper.

All compile cleanly with tsc --noEmit.
**Reasoning:** 

